'''David Bridges''' (born [[22 September]], [[1982]] in [[Huntingdon]]) is an [[England|English]] footballer who plays for [[Stevenage Borough F.C.|Stevenage Borough]] as a [[midfielder]].

==Club career==

Born in [[Huntingdon]], [[Cambridgeshire]], Bridges began his career with local side [[Cambridge United F.C.|Cambridge United]], progressing through the club's [[youth system]].<ref name="David Bridges all time playing career">{{cite news
| title = David Bridges all time playing career
| url = http://www.soccerbase.com/players_details.sd?playerid=30243
| publisher = Soccerbase
| date = 
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> He broke into the [[first-team]] towards the latter stages of the [[2001-02 in English football|2001-02]] season, making his debut as a [[substitute]] in a 1-0 defeat against [[Huddersfield Town F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] at the [[Abbey Stadium]].<ref name="Cambridge 0-1 Huddersfield">{{cite news
| title = Cambridge 0-1 Huddersfield
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_2/1872915.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2002-03-16
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> He played six further games in the same season,<ref name="Cambridge Utd 2001/2002 player appearances">{{cite news
| title = Cambridge Utd 2001/2002 player appearances
| url = http://www.soccerbase.com/squad_season.sd?teamid=483
| publisher = Soccerbase
| date = 
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> scoring his first goal for the [[Cambridgeshire]] outfit in a 2-1 home win against [[Tranmere Rovers F.C.|Tranmere Rovers]].<ref name="Cambridge 2-1 Tranmere">{{cite news
| title = Cambridge 2-1 Tranmere
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_2/1923896.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2002-04-13
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> 

Bridges featured regularly in the opening half of the [[2002-03 in English football|2002-03]] season, playing a total of 25 times and scoring once.<ref name="Cambridge Utd 2002/2003 player appearances">{{cite news
| title = Cambridge Utd 2002/2003 player appearances
| url = http://www.soccerbase.com/squad_season.sd?teamid=483
| publisher = Soccerbase
| date = 
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> However, a persistent [[ankle injury]] cut his run in the [[first-team]] short, and he did not feature from February onwards.<ref name="U's hit by Bridges blow">{{cite news
| title = U's hit by Bridges blow
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/c/cambridge_utd/3004622.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2003-06-19
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> He returned to first-team action in a 1-0 defeat to [[Wycombe Wanderers F.C.|Wycombe Wanderers]] in October 2003,<ref name="Wycombe 1-0 Cambridge">{{cite news
| title = Wycombe 1-0 Cambridge
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/3187248.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2003-10-14
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> and played a further 22 times for the U's throughout the [[2003-04 in English football|2003-04]] campaign.<ref name="Cambridge Utd 2003/2004 player appearances">{{cite news
| title = Cambridge Utd 2003/2004 player appearances
| url = http://www.soccerbase.com/squad_season.sd?teamid=483
| publisher = Soccerbase
| date = 
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> However, Bridges left Cambridge at the end of the season after failing to agree a contract with manager [[Herv<U+00E9> Renard]].

Bridges trialled at a number of clubs before the start of the [[2004-05 in English football|2004-05]] season, most notably [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]] and [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]], without successfully securing a deal.<ref name="Chesterfield warn Bridges">{{cite news
| title = Chesterfield warn Bridges
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/c/chesterfield/3875755.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2004-07-08
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref><ref name="Cobblers look at trio">{{cite news
| title = Cobblers look at trio
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/n/northampton_town/3576150.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2004-08-18
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> After a short stint in [[Latvia]] for [[FK Riga]], Bridges returned to England to join [[Cambridgeshire]] side [[Histon F.C.|Histon]] in March 2005.<ref name="Neil's goal keeps title hopes alive">{{cite news
| title = Neil's goal keeps title hopes alive
| url = http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/cn_sport_football/displayarticle.asp?id=226435
| publisher = Cambridge News
| date = 2005-03-23
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> He scored twice for Histon,<ref name="Now let's go and take title - Fallon">{{cite news
| title = Now let's go and take title - Fallon
| url = http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/cn_sport_football/displayarticle.asp?id=226080
| publisher = Cambridge News
| date = 2005-04-18
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> making eight appearances and helping the club achieve [[promotion]] to the [[Conference South]] in his two months at the club.<ref name="Lucky break puts Histon one game and two divisions from the League">{{cite news
| title = Lucky break puts Histon one game and two divisions from the League
| url = http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/cn_sport_football/displayarticle.asp?id=223352
| publisher = Cambridge News
| date = 2005-04-27
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> He left Histon at the end of the season, and subsequently earned himself a one-year contract to re-join [[Cambridge United F.C.|Cambridge United]], following a successful trial at the club.<ref name="Boss Newman is building Bridges">{{cite news
| title = Boss Newman is building Bridges
| url = http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/cn_sport_camb_utd/displayarticle.asp?id=218539
| publisher = Cambridge News
| date = 2005-07-06
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref>

He made his second debut for Cambridge in a 1-0 defeat at [[Forest Green Rovers F.C.|Forest Green Rovers]],<ref name="Forest Green 1-0 Cambridge">{{cite news
| title = Forest Green 1-0 Cambridge
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/4126814.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2005-08-13
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> and scored in the following two games against both [[Hereford United F.C.|Hereford United]] and [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]].<ref name="Cambridge 2-1 Hereford">{{cite news
| title = Cambridge 2-1 Hereford
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/4148272.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2005-08-16
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref><ref name="Cambridge 3-1 Accrington">{{cite news
| title = Cambridge 3-1 Accrington
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/4148418.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2004-08-20
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> Bridges was a [[first-team]] regular throughout the [[2005-06 in English football|2005-06]] season, and played in 38 matches, scoring seven goals from [[midfielder|midfield]].<ref name="Cambridge Utd 2005/2006 player appearances">{{cite news
| title = Cambridge Utd 2005/2006 player appearances
| url = http://www.soccerbase.com/squad_season.sd?teamid=483
| publisher = Soccerbase
| date = 
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> Consequently, he won the 'Player of the season' award at Cambridge in the same season, and more importantly earned a contract extension in May 2006.<ref name="Cambridge United review of the season">{{cite news
| title = Cambridge United review of the season
| url = http://www.bbc.co.uk/cambridgeshire/content/articles/2006/05/09/cambridge_united_season_review_06_feature.shtml
| publisher = BBC Cambridgeshire
| date = 2006-05-09
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> He continued playing regularly under new manager [[Jimmy Quinn (Northern Irish footballer)|Jimmy Quinn]] in the [[2006-07 in English football|2006-07]] season, scoring three times in 30 appearances.<ref name="Cambridge Utd 2006/2007 player appearances">{{cite news
| title = Cambridge Utd 2006/2007 player appearances
| url = http://www.soccerbase.com/squad_season.sd?teamid=483
| publisher = Soccerbase
| date = 
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> However, he was released by Quinn in May 2007 as he re-vamped the entire squad.<ref name="Castle leaves post at Cambridge">{{cite news
| title = Castle leaves post at Cambridge
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/c/cambridge_utd/6616705.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2007-05-02
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref>

Two months later, Bridges joined [[Conference North]] side [[Kettering Town F.C.|Kettering Town]] on a one-year deal.<ref name="David Bridges playing career">{{cite news
| title = David Bridges Playing career
| url = http://www.soccerbase.com/players_details.sd?playerid=30243
| publisher = Soccerbase
| date = 
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> He was instrumental for the [[Northamptonshire]] club throughtout Kettering's [[2007-08 in English football|2007-08]] league campaign, scoring 11 goals in 39 appearances to help guide Kettering to promotion to the [[Conference National]].<ref name="Poppies march on at Hyde">{{cite news
| title = Poppies march on at Hyde
| url = http://www.northantset.co.uk/sport/Poppies-march-on-at-Hyde.3883322.jp
| publisher = Northants Evening Telegraph
| date = 2008-03-16
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref><ref name="Kettering promoted as champions">{{cite news
| title = Kettering promoted as champions
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/7332649.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2008-04-05
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> He was offered a new contract by manager [[Mark Cooper]], which was rejected, as he opted to join [[Craig Westcarr]] and [[Gary Mills (footballer born 1981)<U+200E>|Gary Mills]] at [[Stevenage Borough F.C.|Stevenage Borough]].<ref name="Stevenage sign defender Anaclet">{{cite news
| title = Stevenage sign defender Anaclet
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/s/stevenage/7398824.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2008-05-13
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref><ref name="New signings confirmed">{{cite news
| title = New signings confirmed
| url = http://www.stevenageborofc.com/index_news_det.php?uk_newsPage=65&news_id=657
| publisher = Stevenage Borough official site
| date = 2008-05-10
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> However, Bridges suffered a [[knee injury]] and missed the first half of the [[2008-09 in English football|2008-09]] season. He eventually made his debut for the [[Hertfordshire]] outfit in a 1-1 draw against [[Oxford United F.C.|Oxford United]] in December 2008, scoring Stevenage's goal.<ref name="Oxford 1-1 Stevenage">{{cite news
| title = Oxford 1-1 Stevenage
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/7779483.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2008-12-20
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref> He played 19 games, scoring six goals before he suffered an injury in another 1-1 draw against Oxford United at [[Broadhall Way]], which ultimately ruled him out for the rest of the season.<ref name="Stevenage 1-1 Oxford">{{cite news
| title = Stevenage 1-1 Oxford
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/7948964.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2009-03-28
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref><ref name="Stevenage Borough 2008/2009 player appearances">{{cite web
| title = Stevenage Borough 2008/2009 player appearances
| url = http://www.soccerbase.com/squad_season.sd?teamid=2499
| publisher = Soccerbase
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref>

==International Career==

Bridges was named in the [[England C national football team|England C]] team, who represent England at [[Non-League football|non-League]] level, in January 2006, for a friendly against Italy, staged at Cambridge's [[Abbey Stadium]], his home ground at the time.<ref name="Bridges secures England call-up">{{cite news
| title = Bridges secures England call-up
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/4712602.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2006-02-14
| accessdate = 2009-08-16}}</ref>

